			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2010</a> paper:</span><br><i>Modelling GLL Parser Implementations</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AdrianJohnstone.html">Adrian Johnstone</a>, <a href="../profile/ElizabethScott.html">Elizabeth Scott</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_4">10.1007/978-3-642-19440-5_4</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagM">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> The central theme is refining a high-level model of the GLL algorithm into practical parser-generator implementations.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly studies time–space tradeoffs and space-efficient data-structure choices for parsers.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It is driven by correctness- and complexity-preserving refinements of an algorithmic model into implementation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
